div.p: Type 0: NULL Value: NULL Size: 0 bytes No data bytes consumed. NULL presence encoded purely in type code.

Integer Types (1-6) Type 1: 8-bit (1 byte) Type 2: 16-bit (2 bytes) Type 3: 24-bit (3 bytes) Type 4: 32-bit (4 bytes) Type 5: 48-bit (6 bytes) Type 6: 64-bit (8 bytes) Big-endian signed integers. Type chosen by value range.
Special Integer Types Type 8: Integer 0 Type 9: Integer 1 Size: 0 bytes each Common values 0 and 1 encoded in type alone. No data bytes needed.
Type 7: IEEE 754 Float Value: 64-bit float Size: 8 bytes Standard IEEE 754 double-precision format. Big-endian byte order.
Type N13 (odd): TEXT Formula: (N - 13) / 2 Example: N=23 5 bytes Length encoded in type. For 5-byte string: serial_type = 13 + (5 2) = 23
Type N12 (even): BLOB Formula: (N - 12) / 2 Example: N=20 4 bytes Binary data of any length. For 4-byte blob: serial_type = 12 + (4 2) = 20
Bytes 5-9 Alice name value (5 bytes) ASCII encoding
Color Legend Header bytes (4 total) Data bytes (7 total)

Row with NULL: INSERT INTO users VALUES (99, NULL, 25) Serialized: 03 00 01 63 19 age: 25 (0x19) id: 99 (0x63) age: type 1 name: type 0 (NULL) header size: 3 Key Insight: NULL occupies 0 data bytes. Only the type code (0) is stored in header.

Variable-Length Integers Value 0-127: 1 byte [0xxxxxxx] Value 128-16383: 2 bytes [1xxxxxxx][0xxxxxxx] Value 16384+: 3+ bytes [1xxxxxxx][1xxxxxxx][0xxxxxxx] ... Max (2-1): 9 bytes High bit = 1: more bytes follow High bit = 0: last byte Example: 300 300 = 0b10 0101100 Encoded: [1 0000010] [0 0101100] = 0x82 0x2C
Header Size (varint) Total bytes in header including this field

Serial Type Codes (one varint per column) Type 0: NULL (0 bytes) Type 1: 8-bit int Type 2: 16-bit int Type 3: 24-bit int Type 4: 32-bit int Type 5: 48-bit int Type 6: 64-bit int Type 7: IEEE 754 float Type 8: Integer 0 (0 bytes) Type 9: Integer 1 (0 bytes) Type N12 even: BLOB Type N13 odd: TEXT
Serialized Column Values Each column's bytes follow in declaration order. Size determined by serial type code in header.
